  "prompt": "What happens when a batsman hit a shot and ball hits the spidercam?",
  "response": "When a batsman hits a shot and the ball strikes the Spidercam:\n\n1. **Dead Ball:** The ball is declared dead immediately. This means that the play stops and no runs can be scored off that delivery. Additionally, no wickets can fall as a result of the ball hitting the Spidercam.\n\n2. **Re-bowling the Delivery:** The specific delivery is then bowled again, effectively providing the batsman a free retry for that ball. This is similar to other instances when the ball hits foreign objects or when play is interrupted.\n\nThe rules are put in place to ensure fairness, given that the interference prevents the ball from continuing its intended course, which could unjustly affect the outcome of the play.",
